CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used for styling and layout of web pages, not directly related to 5G technology. However, if you're building a web application or dashboard to visualize 5G-related data or concepts, CSS can play a crucial role in creating a visually appealing and user-friendly interface.

## Potential CSS Applications for 5G
- *Data Visualization*: Styling charts, graphs, and maps to effectively communicate 5G-related data insights.
- *Network Topology Visualization*: Visualizing 5G network architecture and components using CSS-styled diagrams.
- *Dashboard Design*: Creating a responsive and interactive dashboard to monitor 5G network performance, traffic, and other key metrics.

## Example CSS Code
Here's an example of CSS code for styling a 5G-related dashboard:
/* Global Styles */

* {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
}

/* Dashboard Container */

.dashboard-container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 40px auto;
  padding: 20px;
  background-color: #fff;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

/* Chart and Graph Styles */

.chart-container {
  width: 100%;
  height: 400px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.chart-title {
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: bold;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

/* Responsive Design */

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .dashboard-container {
    margin: 20px auto;
    padding: 10px;
  }
  
  .chart-container {
    height: 300px;
  }
}

This code snippet demonstrates basic CSS styling for a 5G-related dashboard, including layout, typography, and responsive design. The actual CSS code would depend on the specific design requirements and layout of your application.
